               <p>Boyce, a native of <placeName>Oxford</placeName>, matriculated at Christ Church in
                     <date when="1727-07">July 1727</date>, where <persName><ref
                        target="/persons/pers2176.xml"/>CW</persName> was one of his tutors, and
                  received his <seg ana="degree">BA</seg> in <date when="1731">1731</date>. He was
                  part of the &apos;Oxford Methodists&apos; for a time. He went on to earn his <seg
                     ana="degree">MA</seg>, be ordained, and appointed rector of
                     <placeName>Saintbury</placeName>, where he served until his death. See <hi
                     rend="italic">Alumni Oxonienses</hi>; CCEd; and Tyerman, <hi rend="italic"
                     >Oxford Methodists</hi>, 361.</p>
